<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Actor Dick Requests Drug Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ``NewsRadio'' actor Andy Dick has asked a  
judge to consider him for a yearlong drug diversion program that 
could clear him of drug charges. 
</P>
<P>
	Dick, 33, had been scheduled to enter a plea Friday to charges  
including cocaine and marijuana possession and hit-and-run driving. 
</P>
<P>
	Instead, he appeared Thursday in Los Angeles Superior Court and  
asked to be sent to the drug program. 
</P>
<P>
	A decision is expected to be handed down at Dick's arraignment  
Aug. 12. 
</P>
<P>
	Dick was arrested May 15 after his car hit a telephone pole near  
the Hollywood Bowl. Police said Dick appeared intoxicated and tried 
to flee. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
