<HEADLINE> Canseco Sent Home To Rest Bad Back </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Tampa Bay slugger Jose Canseco, who leads the AL  
with 31 home runs, was sent home from the ballpark Saturday to rest 
his chronically ailing back. 
</P>
<P>
	He is listed as day-to-day and it's not yet known how the injury  
will affect his status for Tuesday's All-Star Game. Canseco, 
batting .276 with 69 RBIs, was elected to start as the designated 
hitter. 
</P>
<P>
	Canseco, who celebrated his 35th birthday July 2, came out of  
Friday's game in the eighth inning against Florida with a stiff 
back. He underwent an examination Saturday afternoon and, after 
arriving late to the ballpark, he was given permission to go to his 
Miami home. 
</P>
<P>
	Canseco missed 12 games in June and July last year with similar  
back spasms, but didn't miss a start following the All-Star break. 
He had two separate stints on the DL due to back ailments in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1996, Canseco underwent back surgery to remove fragments and  
also sustained a ruptured disc. 
  	   	
</P>
