<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Longshore Talks Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- The Associated Press, in a July 7 story  
about a longshore workers strike, erroneously quoted a union 
spokesman as saying that a refusal by longshore workers in Los 
Angeles and Long Beach to work overtime or during lunch was in 
sympathy with the Oakland dock workers. 
</P>
<P>
	Spokesman Steve Stallone did confirm that the workers in Los  
Angeles and Long Beach were refusing to work overtime or during 
lunch. But he did not say their action was being taken in sympathy 
with workers who walked off the job in Oakland. 
  	   	
</P>
