<HEADLINE> Dallas 5, Kansas City 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- Dallas scored four times in the final 10 minutes  
as the Burn beat Kansas City 5-0 Saturday night at the Cotton Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
	Jason Kreis, leading the MLS with 36 points, had two goals and  
two assists. Paul Broome and Chad Deering each had a goal and an 
assist, while Ted Eck added a goal. 
</P>
<P>
	The Burn's scoring outburst was the second-quickest in league  
history. The Los Angeles Galaxy scored four times in six minutes on 
June 4, 1998 in an 8-1 victory over the Burn. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm proud of the way the guys played tonight,'' Burn coach  
Dave Dir said. ``We got a little sloppy when they went down to 10 
men, but they eventually wore down and we were able to take 
advantage. This was Kansas City's third game in a week and I 
thought they played very well. The score was not indicative.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Burn (10-9) remains tied with the Chicago Fire in the  
Western Conference race, as Chicago defeated the New York-New 
Jersey MetroStars tonight. Kansas City (4-13) remains in sixth 
place in the West. 
  	   	
