<HEADLINE> Utah State AD Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOGAN, Utah (AP) -- Utah State athletic director Bruce Van De  
Velde resigned Friday to become an associate AD at Oklahoma. 
</P>
<P>
	Van De Velde said he is leaving for his family and for the  
professional opportunity at Oklahoma, where he will be the senior 
associate AD. 
</P>
<P>
	``I appreciate the opportunity to have served as director this  
past year and am grateful for the support shown to the program 
during my time here,'' Van De Velde said. 
</P>
<P>
	His resignation is effective July 28.  
</P>
<P>
	Van De Velde was hired at Utah State just over a year ago to  
replace Chuck Bell, who became AD at San Jose. Before that, Van De 
Velde was an associate AD at Missouri. 
</P>
<P>
	While at Utah State, Van De Velde hired basketball coach Stew  
Morrill, the second-winningest coach in Colorado State's history, 
and women's volleyball coach Tom Peterson, who won the men's 
volleyball national championship while at Penn State. 
  	   	
</P>
