<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Boston Station Drops Imus Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Don Imus got the boot in Bean Town.  
</P>
<P>
	Radio station WEEI-AM is dropping ``Imus in the Morning'' on  
Aug. 24, saying Friday the broadcast veteran has lost his edge. 
</P>
<P>
	``He used to be very fast paced and energetic. He was very  
passionate and the audience was captured by it,'' said Jason Wolfe, 
station program director. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think he's at a point in his life where he's comfortable and  
he wants to do the show for himself. He's got a young child now, 
which has made him a softer personality. I think all of those 
factors have contributed to his ratings decline. It's not 
entertaining anymore.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The show, weekdays from 6-10 a.m., had been No. 1 in the Boston  
market in 1996, but has since dropped from a 10 share to a 4.7 
share. The station has aired the show since 1994. 
</P>
<P>
	Infinity Broadcasting, which owns New York's WFAN-AM, where  
Imus' show originates, expects another Boston station will pick up 
the show. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't think Don Imus will be on the sidelines for long in  
Boston,'' said Infinity executive David Pearlman. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
