<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rapids 2, United 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Jorge Dely Valdes' goal broke a tie in the  
74th minute as the Colorado Rapids beat D.C. United 2-1 Saturday 
night in a match between MLS conference leaders. 
</P>
<P>
	Valdes got a step on United defender Brian Kamler at the top of  
the penalty area. When Kamler offered little resistance, Valdes 
broke through and scored on a soft shot beneath goalie Tom 
Presthus. It was Valdes' seventh goal of the year. 
</P>
<P>
	Colorado improved to 6-3 on the road and has one more road  
victory than it did last season. 
</P>
<P>
	Eastern Conference-leading D.C. (12-7), which has lost four of  
six games, tied the game about two minutes earlier on a goal by 
A.J. Wood. Following Geoff Aunger's cross from the left side, Wood 
hit the last of a series of three headers, bouncing the ball into 
an open net to ruin Rapids goalie Ian Feuer's shutout bid. 
</P>
<P>
	Joey DiGiamarino gave Colorado (12-4), which has won five of  
seven and leads the Western Conference, a 1-0 lead in the 61st 
minute. 
</P>
<P>
	Valdes corralled the rebound of an errant D.C. corner kick from  
the left side and sprung DiGiamarino with a long lead pass. 
DiGiamarino sped past defender Jeff Agoos and converted a low shot 
from the top of the penalty area. 
</P>
<P>
	DiGiamarino's goal came about nine minutes after an apparent  
goal by D.C.'s Roy Lassiter was disallowed because Lassiter was 
ruled offsides. 
</P>
<P>
	Feuer made five saves, three of them in the second half. D.C.  
had six chances in the final five minutes, but could not come up 
with the equalizer. 
</P>
<P>
	Colorado, which dropped its first five regular-season matches  
against United, has now won two straight over D.C. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
