<HEADLINE> Ex-NYC Mayor Koch Leaves Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP)-- Former New York mayor Ed Koch walked out of a  
hospital smiling Saturday, more than a week after suffering a heart 
attack. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm never going to retire. I'm very proud of my career and I  
want to continue adding to it,'' Koch said. ``I'm happy to be going 
home.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Koch suffered the heart attack on July 1. During his hospital  
stay, he underwent two angioplasties, a procedure in which doctors 
place a balloon-tipped catheter in a clogged artery and inflate it 
to remove blockage. 
</P>
<P>
	The former mayor also received a new pacemaker during his stay.  
He got his first pacemaker after a minor stroke in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
	Koch said he plans to resume his daily workouts in about four  
weeks. 
  	   	
</P>
