<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Director Hall Joins Houston Faculty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- Sir Peter Hall, one of the world's foremost  
theater directors, is going back to school. 
</P>
<P>
	The University of Houston School of Theatre announced Hall will  
join its faculty this fall. 
</P>
<P>
	Hall, founder of Britain's Royal Shakespeare Company, will take  
the Lyndall F. Wortham Performing Arts Chair left vacant by the 
February death of director Jose Quintero. 
</P>
<P>
	Hall, who joins three-time Pulitzer Prize-winner Edward Albee  
and Tony-winning Broadway producer Stuart Ostrow at the university, 
will teach courses on Shakespeare and directing. 
</P>
<P>
	``After nearly 50 years of directing, I would like to try to  
share what I have learned,'' Hall said in a statement issued 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Hall, a two-time Tony Award winner, directed the Royal  
Shakespeare Company until 1968 before directing the Royal National 
Theater from 1973-88. His credits also include recent years of 
directing at the Glyndebourne Festival Opera and the Old Vic. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
