today's finals of the women's World Cup. Before taking in the game, 
Clinton relaxed in style in Los Angeles, staying in the Beverly 
Hills compound of supermarket magnate Ron Berkel and golfing with 
actor Sylvester Stallone at a country club. On Thursday, Clinton 
ended a cross-country tour of poor U.S. locations. Today, in his 
weekly radio address, he said preventive medical care must be made 
affordable to older Americans who rely on Medicare. 

