<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Wis. Fire Kills 4 Kids, 1 Adult </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ELLSWORTH, Wis. (AP) -- Four children were killed Saturday when a  
fire engulfed their grandparents' house. The mother of three of the 
children was also killed in the blaze. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire was reported around 12:40 a.m. at the home David and  
Nancy Beyer, both 58, of the town of Salem in the northwest part of 
the state. They escaped the blaze with their 10-year-old 
granddaughter Jordana Beyer, the sheriff's office said. 
</P>
<P>
	The girl was in serious condition Saturday. The Beyers were not  
injured. 
</P>
<P>
	The five people killed included the couple's daughter, Ellymae  
Pickerign, 31; her three children William, 4, Alexis, 23 months and 
Natalie, 11 months; and 9-year-old Joshua Beyer, Jordana's brother. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's the worst fire I've seen since I've been here for 13  
years and just looking at the ages of these children, it's hard to 
deal with,'' sheriff's investigator Dennis Sorenson said. 
</P>
<P>
	The cause of the fire had not been determined but officials did  
not suspect foul play, he said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
