<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Alomar Leaves Rehab Start Early </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ALTOONA, Pa. (AP) -- Cleveland catcher Sandy Alomar left his  
rehab appearance early Saturday night with discomfort in his left 
knee. 
</P>
<P>
	Alomar started Saturday's game against Altoona at catcher but  
left after one at-bat. Alomar threw out a runner at second. 
</P>
<P>
	Alomar joined the Indians Double-A Akron team this week to begin  
a 20-day rehab assignment. He has been on the DL since May 11 with 
a sore left knee and underwent surgery to remove bone chips May 21. 
</P>
<P>
	The game drew a record 7,001 fans to the Blair County Ballpark.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
