<HEADLINE> Latin American Briefs /  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) -- A fire that apparently broke out during a  
riot at a juvenile detention center in southern Chile early 
Saturday had left eight teen-age inmates dead, police reported. 
</P>
<P>
	It was not clear what caused the riot at the Alborada Center for  
Juveniles in Temuco, 420 miles south of the capital, Santiago, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Fire Department commander Freddy Rivas said 22 inmates were in  
the area that was completely destroyed by the fire, and 14 were 
rescued unharmed and transferred to other areas. 
</P>
<P>
	Fire fighters worked for several hours early Saturday to put out  
the fire, while police surrounded the area to prevent escapes. 
</P>
<P>
	------	 
</P>
<P>
	RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) -- A Boeing 727 cargo plane owned by  
Brazilian airline Varig caught fire in an airport hanger, injuring 
seven workers, a company spokesman said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	All the injured were Varig employees who were cleaning the  
aircraft at the Salgado Filho airport in Porto Alegre late Friday, 
the spokesman said on condition of anonymity. The city is 960 miles 
southwest of Rio. 
</P>
<P>
	Flights to and from the airport were unaffected, added the  
spokesman. It was not clear how the fire started. 
</P>
